# Homelab Project Conventions

## Documentation

- All documentation lives in `/docs/` as separate markdown files per topic
- Use clear chapter-based structure (e.g., `01-hardware.md`, `02-network.md`)
- Keep docs updated when making infrastructure changes
- Include decision rationale ("why") not just "what"

## Repository Structure

```
docs/           # Documentation chapters
ansible/        # Ansible playbooks and roles
  inventory/    # Host definitions
  playbooks/    # Setup and maintenance playbooks
  roles/        # Reusable Ansible roles
kubernetes/     # K8s manifests
  apps/         # Application deployments
  infrastructure/  # Cluster infrastructure (ingress, storage, monitoring)
scripts/        # Utility shell scripts
```

## Ansible Conventions

- Use YAML files with `.yml` extension
- Group variables in `group_vars/` and host-specific in `host_vars/`
- Document each playbook's purpose in a comment at the top
- Use roles for reusable configurations

